  "final_screenplay": "INT. NIGHT CLUB - LATE EVENING\n\nThe dimly lit club buzzes with energy as people dance and drink. The music blares from speakers on the ceiling, creating an atmosphere of excitement.\n\nNARRATOR (V.O.)\nWelcome to New York City's most notorious nightspot \u2013 The Inferno Nightclub. Every night, crowds flock here for a wild time that will last until dawn.\n\nCUT TO:\nEXT. NEW YORK CITY STREET - DAYTIME\n\nA young woman named JASMINE walks down the street with her head held high. She is wearing black jeans and a leather jacket as she strides confidently past pedestrians who stare at her in awe.\n\nNARRATOR (V.O.)\nJasmine is one of New York's most successful entrepreneurs, but despite all her achievements, she still feels like something is missing from her life.\n\nCUT TO:\nINT. JASMINE'S OFFICE - DAY\n\nInside the office, Jasmine sits behind a sleek desk with stacks of paperwork in front of her. She takes a sip of coffee as she glances at an email on her computer screen.\n\nJASMINE\n(to herself)\nThis project is going to be huge \u2013 if I can just pull it off.\n\nNARRATOR (V.O.)\nJasmine's latest venture is about to launch, and everything has been planned down to the smallest detail. But even with all her success, she still struggles with feelings of loneliness and emptiness.\n\nCUT TO:\nINT. JASMINE'S APARTMENT - NIGHT\n\nAs Jasmine sits alone in her apartment, she flips through a photo album that holds memories from her past life before The Inferno Nightclub took over as the center of everything.\n\nNARRATOR (V.O.)\nBack then, Jasmine was just another struggling artist trying to make it big. But now, with all her success behind her, something still feels off \u2013 like she's missing out on something bigger.\n\nCUT TO:\nINT. THE INFERNO NIGHTCLUB - LATE EVENING\n\nJasmine walks into The Inferno Nightclub and is immediately hit by the deafening noise of music. She looks around at people dancing wildly as if they were not aware that there was any other option but to have fun.\n\nNARRATOR (V.O.)\nAs Jasmine navigates through this sea of excitement, she feels more alone than ever before.\n\nCUT TO:\nINT. JASMINE'S APARTMENT - NIGHT\n\nJasmine sits on her couch and stares at the photo album in despair as memories flood back into her mind.\n\nNARRATOR (V.O.)\nShe starts to realize that no matter how much success or fame she has, it doesn't fill an empty hole inside of her. It's time for change \u2013 something new must happen!\n\nCUT TO:\nINT. THE INFERNO NIGHTCLUB - LATE EVENING\n\nJasmine walks up on stage in front of the crowd and grabs a microphone.\n\nJASMINE\n(to audience)\nLadies and gentlemen, tonight is going to be different! I want you all to close your eyes...and imagine...\n\nNARRATOR (V.O.)\nWith determination etched across her face, Jasmine prepares herself for what's about to come next \u2013 The biggest performance of her life!\n\nCUT TO:\nINT. JASMINE'S APARTMENT - NIGHT\n\nJasmine sits alone in front of a computer screen as she types rapidly.\n\nJASMINE\n(to herself)\nI'm going back...to where it all began...\n\nNARRATOR (V.O.)\nBack to the days when Jasmine was just an aspiring artist trying desperately hard to make something happen \u2013 because sometimes, you have to go home again before moving forward!\n\nCUT TO:\nINT. JASMINE'S APARTMENT - NIGHT\n\nAs she writes her script for The Inferno Nightclub's reopening night party in pencil on a piece of paper next to the computer screen.\n\nJASMINE\n(to herself)\nThis will be my chance...to show everyone what I'm made out of!\n\nNARRATOR (V.O.)\nAnd with that thought, Jasmine packs up all her belongings and heads back down into The Inferno Nightclub's world \u2013 ready for anything now!",
